{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17472943","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17472943"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:02:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:02:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1588"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582954","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582954"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:02:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:02:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1588"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1588"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.62,0.11,0.1,0.05,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1588"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43784"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1588"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-12-18T07:50:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-11T22:20:14+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2022-07-19T08:46:53+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-25 17:42:39"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1588"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"17831"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28773"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"42"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2179"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"3564"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"5808"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"},{"type":"tags","id":"11631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5374"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6576"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35297"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43087"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44056"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28773"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43784","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43784"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 17-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for evaluation of widespread pain and fatigue which has been troubling her over the last four years. The pain affects multiple joints including knees and shoulders. It worsens as the day progresses. She has dislocated her right shoulder at two occasions and these episodes were managed conservatively. On examination the following sign is observed (Image) along with demonstration of hyperextensibility in multiple joints including elbows and knees. She is able to passively dorsiflex 5th digit beyond 90 degree. The examiner also notes \u0027velvety\u0027 skin and multiple scars on her forehead, chin and legs.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most relevant management step?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Physical therapy","Bisphosphonates","Beta blockers","ACE inhibitors","Dapsone"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is a classical of Ehlers Danlos syndrome (EDS) which is a rare genetic defect in collagen and connective tissue synthesis and function. The skin, joints and blood vessels tend to be affected. The patient is able to \u0027flex\u0027 her thumb to the extent that it can lie flush along her forearm. This patient is able to passively appose the thumb to the flexor surface of the radius as shown in the image.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMost prototypic forms of EDS are characterized by varying degrees of hyperextensibility of large and small joints and are classic findings in EDS. Thus it is critical that hyperextensibility be defined, and differentiating mild \u201cnormal\u201d laxity from hyperextensibility can be challenging. The Beighton score is a clinically useful classification of joint laxity:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E1. Passive dorsiflexion of the fifth digit beyond 90 degrees = one point for each hand\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E2. Passive apposition of the thumbs to the flexor surface of the radius = one point for each hand\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E3. Hyperextension of the elbows beyond 10 degrees = one point for each side\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E4. Hyperextension of the knees beyond 10 degrees = one point for each knee\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E5. Flexion of the trunk forward so that the palms are placed flat on the ground = one point\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA score of five or more points is defined as joint hypermobility.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are no specific treatments for these forms of EDS. Supportive therapy including \u003Cstrong\u003Ephysical therapy\u003C/strong\u003E, however, is essential for preservation of normal joint function and alleviation of joint pain. Planned exercise programs and muscle-strengthening exercises are useful and do much to maintain a positive outlook in these individuals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBisphosphonates\u003C/strong\u003E are not indicated in the management of EDS. They are a part of management of closely related syndromes with recurrent fractures such as in osteogenesis imperfecta.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBeta blockers \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003EACE inhibitors\u003C/strong\u003E are also not indicated in the management of EDS. They are however indicated in management of Marfan syndrome which is another inherited connective tissue disorder. Beta blockers reduce haemodynamic stress on the aortic wall and should be considered in case of aortic dilatation. Add on treatment with ACE inhibitors in these patients has also proven beneficial as shown in studies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDapsone\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated in management of EDS. It is bactericidal, bacteriostatic and anti-inflammatory agent which can be used in the management of cutix laxa - a rare connective tissue disorder affecting the skin.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Ehlers Danlos syndrome is a rare heritable connective tissue disorder which affects joints, skin and the vascular system.","There are no specific treatments for Ehlers Danlos syndrome, however supportive therapy includes physical therapy."],"references":["Firestein GS, Budd RC, Gabriel SE, McInnes IB, O\u0027Dell JR. Kelley and Firestein\u0027s Textbook of Rheumatology: Elsevier Health Sciences; 2016.","Malek S, Reinhold EJ, Pearce GS. The Beighton Score as a measure of generalised joint hypermobility. Rheumatology International. 2021;41:1707\u201316. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33738549/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28773"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1588"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16056"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16056","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16056"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/a81b2c14-4cf8-471e-b67c-8c65f300ea05.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/a81b2c14-4cf8-471e-